column3:
We test these functions in `test/pow_tests.cpp`. OK to keep them there?

ACK

@paveljanik I'm focusing on putting all the code in the consensus building package first and we can take care of the tests when the C API is complete and we separate libconsensus to its own repository like libsecp256k1. So, yes, we should separate the tests at some point, but I'll leave that of the scope of this PR for now.\n
